<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6285] Use factory method to create thread pool for timed login</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6285</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;InternalDriver creates a thread pool for running timed logins like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    private static final ThreadPoolExecutor _executorPool =&lt;br/&gt;
            new ThreadPoolExecutor(0, Integer.MAX_VALUE, 60L, TimeUnit.SECONDS,&lt;br/&gt;
                                   new SynchronousQueue&amp;lt;Runnable&amp;gt;());&lt;br/&gt;
    static &lt;/p&gt;
{
        _executorPool.setThreadFactory(new DaemonThreadFactory());
    }

&lt;p&gt;The java.util.concurrent.Executors class has factory methods that create thread pools and hide the details such as choosing keep-alive time and which kind of queue to use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
